960
01:04:32,728 --> 01:04:35,330
Scott: That was a whole business, right, of selling bullshit cables.

961
01:04:36,751 --> 01:04:40,415
Scott: But it's like, if you've already got some, don't force some on the people.

962
01:04:40,695 --> 01:04:44,578
Scott: And it's not just the cables, but like, you know, I've already got SD cards.

963
01:04:44,598 --> 01:04:46,600
Scott: You don't need to include one with my digital camera.

964
01:04:46,640 --> 01:04:56,779
Rym: People, the companies do include this partly because they see it as a customer service thing, because people who buy technology often don't know a lot and they like don't know how to deal with cables.

965
01:04:58,060 --> 01:05:06,740
Scott: A non technology person who goes to a store and buys a camera and might be upset, like, oh, because this person in the store has now got to upsell them and all this other shit.

966
01:05:08,660 --> 01:05:12,504
Rym: By default, no technology comes with those commodity cables anymore.

967
01:05:12,604 --> 01:05:20,771
