974
01:05:43,161 --> 01:05:55,680
Scott: Yeah, but basically all the accessories that go around a thing need to only, you know, basically should be sold and manufactured separately and distributed and reused for extended periods of time.

975
01:05:55,940 --> 01:06:03,960
Scott: People who buy technology don't end up with a enormous glut of just extra crap that's unnecessary that they then have to redistribute.

976
01:06:05,260 --> 01:06:05,421
Rym: Yep.

977
01:06:05,841 --> 01:06:11,250
Rym: So the moral of all this, if you got a ways one, don't buy useless shit you don't need.

978
01:06:11,290 --> 01:06:17,120
Rym: But if you got a bunch of it, which a lot of you probably do, especially if you're a nerd, you were hoarding it and now it's time to get rid of it.

